statement.p:
Let f(x) = x^2 and let g(x) = \frac{1}{x}. Express each of the following functions as a transformation of f or g. For instance, the function y = \left( x-1 \right)^2 can be expressed as y = f(x+1).



    y = (x-4)^2



    y = \frac{3}{x}



    y = x^2 + 5



    y = \frac{1}{x-1}



    y = 2 + 7x^2



    y = \frac{1}{5x}
